.3</span> Choinix</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">χοῖνιξ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(choinix)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">\n          <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a>: The <em>choinix</em> was approximately equal to a liter or a quart, and it is possible to make a straight substitution without changing the numbers.</h2>\n</div>",
